# Migration Monorepo Conventions

## Principles

- Cypress is the **baseline**; Playwright is the **target**
- No real test logic in scaffold phase — placeholders and TODOs only until implementation PRs
- All decisions documented as ADRs in `migration/adr/`
- Empirical data (flakiness, duration, cost) drives decommission timing — not opinion

## Secrets & Artifacts

- Never commit `.env`, JWTs, or `storageState` files
- Never commit `playwright-report/`, `test-results/`, `cypress/screenshots/`, `cypress/videos/`, or Allure output
- CI credentials via GitHub Secrets only

## Documentation

- Analysis docs use structured sections and tables
- Architecture docs use Mermaid in markdown — no PNG diagrams
- ADRs follow Context / Decision / Consequences template

## Environment

- All tests run against locally hosted Conduit (ADR-005)
- No dependency on public demo endpoints
